  "articleSummary": "The article presents a tutorial on securing Docker hosts using **UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall)** on Debian/Ubuntu systems, emphasizing step-by-step configuration of firewall rules to control traffic to and from Docker containers. Key points include installing UFW, defining inbound/outbound policies (e.g., blocking all traffic by default), allowing specific ports (SSH, HTTP/HTTPS), and forwarding traffic to Dockerized applications. The tone is practical and instructional, with warnings about avoiding SSH lockout and testing firewall rules via `nmap`. The intended audience is system administrators or DevOps engineers managing Docker environments, requiring a balance of security and accessibility. Recurring metaphors include \"block all the things\" and \"forward traffic\" to reinforce security-first principles.",
